FBIS4-50712 "drchi098_p_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 Central-South Region Guangdong's Zhuhai Eases Visa Requirements for Tourists Guangdong's Zhuhai Eases Visa Requirements for Tourists HK1905145094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1403 GMT 19 May 94 HK1905145094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE English BFN [Text] Zhuhai, May 19 (CNS) -- Zhuhai, the Special Economic Zone city in Guangdong Province, which was recently named "Tourism City" by the National Tourism Administration, has announced that foreign tourists holding unsigned visas are allowed to stay in the city within three days and this regulation will go into effect next month. According to Mayor of Zhuhai, Mr. Liang Guangda, the above measure is aimed at further opening the city to the outside world and vitalizing tourism industry there and is an important step for the smooth implementation of exemption of visa for overseas visitors. The city has seen a graudal increase of foreign tourists and the number of such tourists last year reached 60,000. With the implementation of the above measure, foreign visitors to the city this year are expected to be over one million.
